{{Taxobox | image = File:Hemimastix amphikineta.png | image_caption = ''[[Hemimastix amphikineta]]'', redrawn from Foissner et al., 1988 | domain = [[Eukaryota]] | unranked_regnum = [[Hemimastigophora]] | unranked_regnum_authority = Foissner et al. 1988 | subdivision_ranks = Order, Family and Genera | subdivision = * [[Hemimastigida]] **[[Spironemidae]] ***''[[Hemimastix]]'' ***''[[Paramastix]]'' ***[[Spironemidae|''Spironema'']] ***''[[Stereonema]]'' }}
'''''Hemimastigophora''''' is a group of [[eukaryotic]] organisms.<ref name=":0">{{cite journal|url=https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-018-0708-8|title=Hemimastigophora is a novel supra-kingdom-level lineage of eukaryotes|first1=Gordon|last1=Lax|first2=Yana|last2=Eglit|first3=Laura|last3=Eme|first4=Erin M.|last4=Bertrand|first5=Andrew J.|last5=Roger|first6=Alastair G. B.|last6=Simpson|date=14 November 2018|journal=Nature|pages=1|accessdate=25 November 2018|doi=10.1038/s41586-018-0708-8|pmid=30429611}}</ref> It was established in 1988 by Foissner et al., as a new [[phylum]] with a single family, [[Spironemidae]].<ref name=":1">http://www.wfoissner.at/data_prot/Foissner_Foissner_1993_422-438.pdf</ref> Its placement on the eukaryote [[Tree of life (biology)|tree of life]] was unclear, but the authors suggested that the structure of its [[Pellicle (biology)|pellicle]] and [[cell nucleus]] indicated a close relationship with [[Euglenozoa]]. For thirty years after the erection of the group, no genetic information was available. During that time, researchers proposed that it should be classified in, or near, an assortment of other groups, including the [[Alveolate|alveolates]], [[Apusozoa|apusomonads]], [[Ancyromonadida|ancyromonads]], and [[Rhizaria]].<ref name=":0" />
In an article published in 2018, it was announced that a new hemimastigophoran species, [[Hemimastix kukwesjijk|''Hemimastix kukwesjijk'']], had been discovered in a [[Nova Scotia|Nova Scotian]] soil sample, and successfully cultivated in the laboratory. A second hemimastigophoran, a new species of [[Spironemidae|''Spironema'']], was found in the same sample. [[Phylogenomics|Phylogenomic]] analyses of the two organisms revealed that Hemimastigophora is a very ancient lineage, which diverged from the other eukaryotes at such an early date that the group should be classified at the supra-kingdom level.<ref name=":0" />
